# BACS 200 - Project #7 - Building Templates

Templates help you build new websites from code written earlier.

This project requires that you build a template library and then apply the templates to all pages on your website.


## Template Library

### Create a directory
* Create a directory named 'bacs200/templates'
* Create an index file for the directory, named 'bacs200/templates/index.html'


### Standard Page Templates
* Build files with reusable code
* Complete Pages
    * html.html - Just enough to validate
    * page.html - Page with stylesheet
    * semantic.html - Add semantic elements (header, main, footer)
    * blog.html - Superset of all page features
   
   
### Standard Component Templates
* Build files with reusable code 
* HTML Fragments
    * header.html - Banner layout
    * main.html - Main page content (section, articles, aside)
    * footer.html - Footer for page
    * menu-top.html - Build top menu with CSS
    * menu-side.html - Build side menu with CSS
   
   
### Template Index Page
* Template Index should build on the blog.html template file
* Create h2 for Pages, Components
* Add bullet lists for Complete Pages and HTML Fragments
* Link each template into the index page


 
## Applying Templates

### Your website files
* index.html
* inspire.html
* amuse.html
* educate.html
* pets/index.html
* templates/index.html


### Projects Page
* Create a directory named 'projects'
* Create a page named 'projects/index.html'
* Use the 'blog.html' template
* Create links
    * inspire.html
    * amuse.html
    * educate.html
    * pets/index.html
    * templates/index.html


### Build a Top Menu
* Create a top menu in menu.html 
* Menu items: Home, Projects, Templates


### Apply the Blog Template
* Link to Home at "bacs200/index.html"
* Use the code in each page
    * index.html
    * projects/index.html
    * templates/index.html


### Build a Side Menu
* In the projects/index.html build a side menu
* Link to all of the projects in your directory


### Apply the Side Menu 
* Set the side menu to jump between projects
    * inspire.html
    * amuse.html
    * educate.html
    * pets/index.html
    * templates/index.html


### Requirements
* Page exists at URL
* Page is Valid HTML & CSS & No Bad Links
* Styles for: Home, Project Pages
* Source code matches the requirements
* Master Page template
* Header template
* Main template
* Footer template
* Article template
* Menu template
